imageRy

Duccio Rocchini, Giovanni Nocera, Elisa Thouverai

2023-07-05

Background

The imageRy R package has been thought to speed up teaching activities, avoiding import/export processes of imagery, providing a catalogue of different imagery coming out from the Earth Observatory site of the NASA, as well as from analysed Sentinel-2 data.

Note In order to install the package you might refer to GitHub by the devtools package as:

devtools::install_github("ducciorocchini/imageRy")

Note Need a guide about devtools? Here it is.

Including plots from the imageRy R package

Once the imageRy R package has been installed the data are ready available-

library(imageRy)
## Loading required package: raster
## Loading required package: sp
data(duccio)

The list of data is available here.

library(raster)
plotRGB(duccio, 1, 2, 3, stretch="lin")
